cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.DL, cs.CL

This paper is about building a searchable archive of tweets, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as indexing and searching. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with social media research, which falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and sound and music computing (cs.SD). The use of APIs and programming languages suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of digital libraries (cs.DL) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
